Wash and dry all produce.

Zest and quarter @lemon{1}. Finely chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}. Halve, peel, and finely
dice @yellow onion{1}. Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove} and @ginger{1%thumb}.
Roughly chop @spinach{2.5%ounce}. Drain and rinse @chickpeas{13.4%ounce}.

== Spiced Cilantro Yogurt Sauce ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine @yogurt{2%tablespoon}, @sour cream{2%tablespoon},
a squeeze of lemon juice, a pinch of @garam masala{1%teaspoon} (you'll use more
later), a pinch of cilantro, and lemon zest to taste. Add water 1 tsp at a time
until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with @salt{pinch} and
@pepper{pinch}.

== Lemon Raisin Basmati Rice ==

Melt @butter{1%tablespoon} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add half the
onion, half the garlic, half the ginger, and a big pinch of @salt{pinch}. Cook,
stirring, until softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add @basmati rice{1/2%cup} and @golden raisins{1%ounce}; stir to coat.

Stir in @water{3/4%cup} and another big pinch of salt. Bring to a boil, then
cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Chickpea & Spinach Fritters ==

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{},
preferably heavy-bottomed, over medium-high heat. Add spinach, remaining onion,
remaining garlic, and remaining ginger. Cook until slightly softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add @curry powder{1%tablespoon}, remaining garam masala, and a pinch of salt;
cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Turn off heat; remove from pan. Wash out pan.

Place chickpeas in a #large bowl{}. Mash with a #potato masher{} or #fork{}
until almost smooth. (TIP: It's OK if there are still some larger pieces.) Stir
in spinach and aromatics, @tempura mix{82%g}, remaining cilantro, @sugar{1/2%teaspoon},
and @water{1/3%cup} until thoroughly combined. Season with @salt{3/4%tsp} and
@pepper{}. (For 4, use 1 1/2 tsp salt.) TIP: Batter should be thick but not dry.
Add more water 1 TBSP at a time as needed.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for aromatics over medium-high heat. Once pan
is hot, carefully add 1/4-cup scoops of chickpea batter, gently pressing to
flatten. Cook until golden brown and crisp, ~{3-4%minutes} per side. TIP: You
may need to work in batches, adding another drizzle of oil before each batch.

Transfer to a #paper-towel-lined plate{}.

== To Serve ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} and remaining lemon zest
to taste. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

Divide rice between plates and top with chickpea and spinach fritters. Drizzle
with spiced cilantro yogurt sauce. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.